The paper discusses the challenges of modelling and testing cyber-physical systems, which involves software and hardware components. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE), Robotics (cs.RO), or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on introducing human-centred considerations into the modelling and testing process, which suggests that it could also belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the importance of remote integration and testing, which suggests that it could also belong to the Embedded Systems (cs.ET) sub-category.
